STAMPY worked on one of the consoles, looking over the lights and
diodes. "Man I wish Longrack was here."

There was a nod from SHARPEDGE, "Yeah, but he's not. We're going to
have to figure this out for ourselves."

SHARPEDGE looked over at NIGHTLIGHT as his partner pulled a few
switches experimentally. The energy in the cylinder flickered and then
weakened. "We're getting somewhere."

That's when a small alarm began to go off.

"It's time to go." SHARPEDGE said.

STAMPY nodded as he quickly moved over to the Cylinder and placed
several grenades around it.

SHARPEDGE nodded, they just didn't have the skills, hopefully they
could get far enough away before it blows.

"30 astro seconds." STAMPY said.

SHAPREDGE grunted, "Good, let's go then . . . "

The door to the room slid open revealing three Sharkticon guards with
weapons facing into the room!

(TAG)

- Preston
